| HistoryText             = 
===Formation===
Originally a division of the [[X-Men (Earth-616)|X-Men]] sanctioned by [[Scott Summers (Earth-616)|Cyclops]] and tasked with the mission to save [[Homo sapiens|humanity]] from various extinction level threats. This team roster included some of the most powerful mutants on the planet.{{r|Uncanny X-Men Vol 2 #1}}

[[File:Uncanny X-Men Vol 2 1 Textless.jpg|left|thumb|200px|The original Extinction Team assembled]]
The teams first major missions included protecting the [[Tiamut (Earth-616)|Dreaming Celestial]] from [[Nathaniel Essex (Earth-616)|Sinister]],{{r|Uncanny X-Men Vol 2 #1|#3}} attempting to save a small town from a lone [[Phalanx (Race)|Phalanx]],{{r|Uncanny X-Men Vol 2 #4}} investigating [[Tabula Rasa (Location)|Tabula Rasa]],{{r|Uncanny X-Men Vol 2 #5|#8}} aiding the [[Avengers (Earth-616)|Avengers]] in battling the [[Dire Wraiths]],{{r|Uncanny X-Men Vol 2 #9}} and capturing [[Sentient World Observation and Response Department (Earth-616)|S.W.O.R.D.]]'s escapee, [[Unit (Earth-616)|Unit]].{{r|Uncanny X-Men Vol 2 #10}}

The Extinction Team, along with the other [[Utopia (X-Men Base)|Utopian]] [[X-Men (Earth-616)|X-Men]], came into direct conflict with the [[Avengers (Earth-616)|Avengers]] when, fearing the imminent return of the [[Phoenix Force (Earth-616)|Phoenix Force]], [[Steven Rogers (Earth-616)|Captain America]] arrived on Utopia demanding to take [[Hope Summers (Earth-616)|Hope Summers]] into custody. Battle broke out ending with Hope's escape and the X-Men's retreat.{{r|Avengers vs. X-Men #1|#4}}{{r|Uncanny X-Men Vol 2 #11|#12}} 

While on the run, [[Scott Summers (Earth-616)|Cyclops]] discovered Hope was heading to the [[Moon]] to meet the Phoenix head-on. Taking [[Illyana Rasputina (Earth-616)|Magik]], [[Piotr Rasputin (Earth-616)|Colossus]], [[Emma Frost (Earth-616)|Emma Frost]] and [[Namor McKenzie (Earth-616)|Namor]], he headed to the Moon to aid her. Upon arriving, the Avengers ambushed the Extinction Team, and [[Anthony Stark (Earth-616)|Iron Man]] attempted to disperse the Phoenix. Ultimately the attempt resulted in the Phoenix being split into the five present X-Men and the [[Phoenix Five (Earth-616)|Phoenix Five]] were created.{{r|Avengers vs. X-Men #5}}{{r|Uncanny X-Men Vol 2 #13}} 

===Phoenix Five===
As the Phoenix Five, Cyclops and the others began to bring peace, prosperity and bounty to the world. Utopia became a sterling example of peace and began flying over the [[San Francisco Bay]]. They also began searching out and imprisoning the Avengers.{{r|Avengers vs. X-Men #6|#7}}{{r|X-Men: Legacy #268|270}}{{r|Wolverine and the X-Men #12}} The Extinction Team and Phoenix Five even destroyed Sinister's clone army, [[Celestial]] machine and Sinister London in the [[Subterranea|Moloid Caverns]].{{r|Uncanny X-Men Vol 2 #15|#17}}

[[File:Phoenix Five (Earth-616) and Hope Summers (Earth-616) from Avengers vs. X-Men Vol 1 5 0001.png|right|thumb|200px|The [[Phoenix Five (Earth-616)|Phoenix Five]]]]
Unfortunately, the Phoenix Five soon became corrupted. Magik began torturing her Avengers prisoners with [[Limbo (Demonic)|Limbo]] [[Demons]] she summoned,{{r|X-Men: Legacy #269|270}}{{r|Avengers vs. X-Men #9}} Colossus began threatening loved ones,{{r|Wolverine and the X-Men #14}} Emma began policing individuals' thoughts, and Namor declared war between [[Atlantis]] and [[Wakanda]].{{r|Avengers vs. X-Men #8}} Eventually, Namor lost his portion of the Phoenix when attacked with all the Avengers' firepower,{{r|Avengers vs. X-Men #8}} and Magik and Colossus lost theirs when they turned on each other.{{r|Avengers vs. X-Men #9}}

With only two Phoenixes left, Cyclops, fearing the [[Chaos]] [[Magic]] of the [[Wanda Maximoff (Earth-616)|Scarlet Witch]] and [[Iron Fist]]/[[Dragon Lord]] training of Hope Summers, turned on Emma taking her portion of the Phoenix and becoming Dark Phoenix. Cyclops killed [[Charles Xavier (Earth-616)|Professor X]] before trying to end the world. He was only narrowly stopped by Scarlet Witch and Hope Summers dissipating the Phoenix energy and reigniting the [[Homo Superior|mutant population]] around the [[Earth|world]] once more.{{r|Avengers vs. X-Men #10|#12}}{{r|Uncanny X-Men Vol 2 #18|#19}}{{r|Wolverine and the X-Men #15}}

===Consequences===
After the murder of Professor X, Cyclops and Emma Frost were imprisoned separately, [[Elizabeth Braddock (Earth-616)|Psylocke]] and [[Ororo Munroe (Earth-616)|Storm]] turned themselves into the custody of the X-Men, [[Max Eisenhardt (Earth-616)|Magneto]], Namor{{r|AvX: Consequences #1}} and [[Danger (Earth-616)|Danger]] went AWOL, and Magik freed Colossus from [[Cyttorak (Earth-616)|Cyttorak]] before separate parting ways.{{r|Uncanny X-Men Vol 2 #20}} 

[[File:X-Men (New Charles Xavier School) (Earth-616) from AvX Consequences Vol 1 5 001.jpg|thumb|left|After Avengers vs. X-Men]]
Initially, Cyclops was content to remain a political prisoner or become a martyr.{{r|AvX: Consequences #1|#3}} However, when it became clear that the world's [[Homo Superior|new mutant population]] needed protection, he ordered his own escape via Magneto, Magik and Danger. Now with Magneto and Magik, Cyclops is again ready to protect and save a world that now hates and fears him.{{r|AvX: Consequences #4|#5}}

===Mutant Rebellion===
Cyclops, Magneto and Magik go about liberating the unjustly imprisoned mutants and offering them aid with their powers and a place in Cyclops' new team. When attempting to liberate [[Emma Frost (Earth-616)|Emma Frost]], Cyclops and Magneto lost control of their powers. Emma revealed that she was going through a similar problem and told them that the Phoenix had altered their powers. Magik revealed that her powers were changing as well, but for the better, as she had gained the ability to summon energies from Limbo atop of her existing powers.{{r|All-New X-Men #3}}

[[File:Uncanny X-Men Special Vol 1 1 Brooks Variant Textless.jpg|thumb|right]]
As Cyclops and Magneto left to find another new mutant, they were confronted by a younger Cyclops and younger versions of the other five original X-Men. While confronting the five young X-Men, [[Jean Grey (Earth-616)|the young Jean Grey]] lost control of her powers and tossed Cyclops away with her telekinesis. This caused Cyclops to lose his visor and he began firing optic blasts wildly, leading the young X-Men to believe that he was attacking them. Magneto disposed of them and ordered Magik to transport him and Cyclops back to headquarters. Cyclops later freed Emma and recruited more young mutants to his team.{{r|Uncanny X-Men Vol 3 #4}}

===Darkchilde and S.H.I.E.L.D.===
Later, the team was accidentally transported to Limbo by Magik due to her broken powers. After facing Dormammu, the team was able to escape but Goldballs left due to not being able to handle being an X-Man. After this, the team added David Bond to their ranks and gave him the code-name Hijack. Soon after, Fabio rejoined the team.{{r|Uncanny X-Men Vol 3 #5|7}}

===Battle of the Atom===
Later on, his team of X-Men encountered a team of X-Men from the future who told them they were here to prevent a disaster from happening because of the past X-Men being in the present time. After some investigating and meeting another team calling themselves the X-Men, it was revealed that the first former team were actually the future Brotherhood. During this time, the Stepford Cuckoos and the past Angel joined Cyclops's team. In the end, Scott's team and Wolverine's team defeated the future Brotherhood and the real future X-Men went back to their own time. Also, Kitty, Lockheed and the rest of the past X-Men left the Jean Grey School to join Scott's team because of Logan's actions and mistrust. After a mission Magneto left the team to do things on his own terms. After this, Hijack was kicked off the team after almost putting them in danger. After trying to adjust to a normal life again, he was interrogated by Maria Hill of SHIELD for the location of Cyclops's team. The team did rescue him and he, along with Dazzler rejoined them.{{r|Uncanny X-Men Vol 3 #22}}

===AXIS===
After Scarlet Witch and Dr. Doom cast an inversion spell during a fight against the [[Johann Shmidt (Clone) (Earth-616)|Red Onslaught]], the moral compass of the heroes and villains present during the battle were inverted.{{r|Avengers & X-Men: AXIS #3}} As a consequence of the inversion, both X-Men teams reunited in order to wage war against humanity.{{r|Avengers & X-Men: AXIS #4}}

The inverted X-Men planned on using a gene bomb to kill everyone on the Earth who wasn't a mutant.{{r|Avengers & X-Men: AXIS Vol 1 6}} The [[Astonishing Avengers (Earth-616)|Astonishing Avengers]] tried to stop them, and even though they were defeated in combat,{{r|Avengers & X-Men: AXIS Vol 1 7}} managed to prevent the bomb from fulfilling its purpose.{{r|Avengers & X-Men: AXIS Vol 1 8}} The [[Axis (Avengers) (Earth-616)|Axis]], the group of inverted Avengers, arrived to New York to kill the inverted X-Men. During the fight, a reinversion spell was cast by Doctor Doom and the Scarlet Witch, with the help of the inverted Red Skull, turning almost everybody back to normal. After the event, Cyclops' X-Men returned to Alberta, Canada.{{r|Avengers & X-Men: AXIS Vol 1 9}}

===The Utopians===
The X-Men were reached out by [[Strategic Homeland Intervention, Enforcement and Logistics Division (Earth-616)|S.H.I.E.L.D.]] to investigate Utopia after a recon team went missing. The X-Men teleported to the island, and initially engaged the Utopians. After talking it out and discovering the Utopians wanted nothing but to be safe and undisturbed, the X-Men offered them a place at the [[Weapon X Facility|New Charles Xavier School]], which they gladly accepted.{{r|All-New X-Men #41}}

===The Last Will and Testament of Charles Xavier===
After the discovery of the Last Will and Testament of Charles Xavier,{{r|Uncanny X-Men Vol 3 23}} it was revealed Charles had left all of his possessions to Scott.{{r|Uncanny X-Men Vol 3 31}} Racked by guilt, Scott left all of those possessions to the Jean Grey School, decided to disband his group of X-Men, suggesting them to move to the Jean Grey School, and planned to turn himself in for the death of Charles.{{r|Uncanny X-Men Vol 3 32}}

